# GitHub Linguist — language-bar classification.
#
# This repo is a Claude Code plugin made almost entirely of Markdown (README, CLAUDE.md,
# SKILL.md, docs, ADRs) plus generation templates. It contains no Go.
#
# Two Linguist defaults combine to mislabel it as "Go Template 100%":
#   1. Markdown is a `prose` language, excluded from the language bar by default.
#   2. The *.tpl templates use `{{KEY}}` placeholders — the same double-brace syntax as
#      Go's text/template — so Linguist detects them as "Go Template", leaving them as the
#      only counted files.
#
# Fix: the *.tpl files are Markdown with placeholders (not Go), and we want the bar to
# reflect that the project is Markdown.

*.tpl linguist-language=Markdown
*.tpl linguist-detectable=true
*.md  linguist-detectable=true
